## New tables must paginate

Any **new screen** that lists entities in a **`Table`** from [`components/ui/table.tsx`](components/ui/table.tsx) (or equivalent split desktop table + mobile list fed from the same query) **must** include pagination — do not ship unbounded full-table loads for directories that can grow.

### Defaults (match existing)

- **Page size:** [`SETTINGS_TABLE_PAGE_SIZE`](lib/pagination/constants.ts) (**10**). Do not introduce ad‑hoc sizes without a maintainer decision.
- **Footer UI:** [`SettingsTablePagination`](components/settings/settings-table-pagination.tsx) with a `buildHref(nextPage)` that preserves current query params (`q`, filters, etc.).
- **URL state:** Drive **`page`** (and search/filter params) via **`searchParams`** on the route (see [`app/(app)/settings/categories/page.tsx`](app/(app)/settings/categories/page.tsx), [`app/(app)/settings/users/page.tsx`](app/(app)/settings/users/page.tsx)). Reset **`page` to `1`** when search or filters change.
- **Supabase:** Use **`.select(..., { count: 'exact' })`**, **`.order(...)`**, and **`.range(from, to)`** for the efficient path; clamp **`page`** when it exceeds `totalPages` (same retry pattern as those pages). If filters require Auth-only fields (e.g. ban state), document the hybrid approach like [`loadOrgUsersListForAdmin`](lib/org-users/load-org-users.ts) (SQL page vs full merge + slice).

### Reference implementations

- Categories: [`components/settings/categories-management.tsx`](components/settings/categories-management.tsx) + categories settings page.
- Users: [`components/settings/users-management.tsx`](components/settings/users-management.tsx) + users settings page.

### Exceptions

- Tiny fixed sets (e.g. &lt; 15 rows **guaranteed** by product, not data) may skip pagination only if called out explicitly in the task; default is **always paginate** for user- or admin-managed lists.
